design professor at MIT.

31
00:01:33,450 --> 00:01:37,353
So FNAP, facts not assertions, please.

32
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:40,297
My father once said to me,

33
00:01:40,297 --> 00:01:43,530
"Have a plan and be ready to change it,"

34
00:01:43,530 --> 00:01:46,380
and that really stuck
with me from an early age.

35
00:01:46,380 --> 00:01:47,700
The ability to be flexible

36
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:50,970
and pivot when something
isn't going the way we planned

37
00:01:50,970 --> 00:01:53,130
is crucial to the design process

38
00:01:53,130 --> 00:01:55,680
and really is a skill
that we try to foster

39
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:57,230
in each of our design students.

40
00:01:58,170 --> 00:02:00,810
In our product design class at MIT,

41
00:02:00,810 --> 00:02:03,690
teams explore hundreds of product ideas,

42
00:02:03,690 --> 00:02:05,220
you might say plans,

43
00:02:05,220 --> 00:02:06,690
before deciding which

44
00:02:06,690 --> 00:02:10,200
final single product
direction they'll take.

45
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:12,750
Next week, you're gonna
be deciding on your

46
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:13,740
product direction

47
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:16,500
for the rest of our product
development process.

48
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:18,960
It's about working together

49
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:23,770
and really making the best
informed decision that you can.

50
00:02:23,770 --> 00:02:27,390
(students cheering)
(lively music)

51
00:02:27,390 --> 00:02:30,360
