end up on the cutting board.

54
00:02:38,490 --> 00:02:42,510
Each team member will have
plans and then change them.

55
00:02:42,510 --> 00:02:44,550
How do we make these decisions?

56
00:02:44,550 --> 00:02:46,590
This is a hard question,

57
00:02:46,590 --> 00:02:50,820
but FNAP is one thinking
tool that we provide.

58
00:02:50,820 --> 00:02:55,820
So FNAP, what that means is
facts not assertions, please.

59
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:57,750
And so, a fact is something

60
00:02:57,750 --> 00:03:01,200
that's really a known
or demonstrated truth,

61
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:04,260
and an assertion is really
something we believe in

62
00:03:04,260 --> 00:03:08,613
that we can often very convincingly
make sound like a fact.

63
00:03:09,514 --> 00:03:11,064
- [Student] Okay, big yay, yay.

64
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:16,170
